§ Result ⦉
<statement type='proposition'>
  ‖ Suppose $X$ is a complete inner product space, $A ⊂ X$
    closed and convex, and $x ∈ X$. ⦉

  ‖ There exists a unique $z ∈ X$ satisfying
    ◇ ⦊
      ‖ d(z, x) = ∈f_{y ∈ A} d(y, x). ⦉
    ⦉⦉
</statement>
